OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782866866
OL,3,CMothers of women killed by their
OL,4,Cpartners welcome sentencing changes
OL,6,FEvery now and then in this job, you
OL,7,Fmeet people whose courage in the face
OL,8,Fof abject grief and torment takes your
OL,9,Fbreath away.
OL,11,FThree years ago, I found myself at a
OL,12,Fkitchen table with three mothers:
OL,13,FElaine Newborough, Julie Devey and
OL,14,FCarole Gould.
OL,16,FUp until the worst moments in their
OL,17,Flives, they had been complete
OL,18,Fstrangers.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G1/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31502
SC,0002
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782866866
OL,3,CMothers of women killed by their
OL,4,Cpartners welcome sentencing changes
OL,6,FBut they had connected over their
OL,7,Foutrage over one fact: the jail
OL,8,Fsentences their daughter's partners
OL,9,Fhad received after they had murdered
OL,10,Fthem with a knife.
OL,12,FThey had been shocked to discover that
OL,13,Fif a woman is stabbed to death in the
OL,14,Fstreet by a stranger, the starting
OL,15,Fpoint for sentencing is 25 years.
OL,17,FBut if the same woman is stabbed to
OL,18,Fdeath with a kitchen knife by a
OL,19,Fpartner in her own home, the starting
OL,20,Fpoint for sentencing is 15 years.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G2/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,316,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31503
SC,0003
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F315A1782866866
OL,3,CMothers of women killed by their
OL,4,Cpartners welcome sentencing changes
OL,6,FIt was a disparity they felt they
OL,7,Fcouldn't stay silent about, even if it
OL,8,Fcost them dearly in deeper pain to
OL,9,Fspeak out.
OL,11,FThey saw the law as discriminatory
OL,12,Fagainst women: where women's lives
OL,13,Flost to domestic violence were valued
OL,14,Fless highly than men murdered in
OL,15,Fstreet attacks by a stranger.
OL,17,FWeeping as they spoke, Elaine, Julie
OL,18,Fand Carole told us the stories of
OL,19,Ftheir daughters for ITV's Tonight
OL,20,Fprogramme.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G3/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
